createWikiBootstrap

public java.lang.String createWikiBootstrap(java.util.List<WikiStorageBulkServiceImpl.WikiPageMeta> selectedPages)
                                     throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                                            java.lang.IllegalStateException,
                                            java.lang.Exception
Create a wiki bootstrap called wikibootstrapTIMESTAMP.zip that contains the most recent revision of the selected pages. The internal structure of the zip file is such that it can be used by the solution service, i.e. pages are in the sub directory "data/wikiBootstrap/". The Zip file is written to WIKIEXPORT_STORAGE

Parameters:
selectedPages -
Returns:
the filename, e.g. wikiBootstrapTIMESTAMP.zip
Throws:
java.lang.Exception - if an I/O error occurs
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the selections are empty or null
java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the wiki directory could not be created

restoreLatestBootstrap

public boolean restoreLatestBootstrap(org.openrdf.model.URI name)
                               throws java.io.IOException
Restore the latest bootstrap version iff a) the current page is a user page b) there exists some bootstrap version c) the content of the latest version and the bootstrap are actually different This method also writes the semantic link differences into the triple store

Parameters:
name -
Returns:
true if the restore operation was successful, false if the operation was not performed as one of the conditions above was not met
Throws:
java.io.IOException
{@link - IllegalStateException} if the content of current and bootstrap are identical

Create a wiki bootstrap called wikibootstrapTIMESTAMP that contains all user edited pages (i.e. excluding the ones that are imported by another bootstrap)

Description copied from interface: WikiStorageBulkService
Import wiki-files within directories matching the following path: dir\"wikiBootstrap"* Name of wiki files are assumed to be url-encoded URIs.

Specified by:
bootstrapWiki in interface WikiStorageBulkService
Parameters:
workingDir - the base directory. All directories within this base directory with a prefix of "wikiBootstrap" are searched for wiki pages to import
artifactVersion - a version string indicating for instance the name and the version of the solution artifact or the software component
